import TimeLineElement from "../components/cv/TimeLine.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Resume" sideBarActiveItemID="cv">
  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Profile</div>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-10 text-justify">
    Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna
    aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis
    aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat
    cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum.
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Education</div>
  </div>

  <div class="time-line-container grid gap-4 mb-10">
    <TimeLineElement
      title="PhD in Systems and Information Engineering"
      subtitle="Sep. 2022 to May. 2027 at University Of Virginia, Charlottesville, USA (GPA: 4.0)"
    />
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Bachelor in Computer Science with High Distinction (Minor in Psychology)"
      subtitle="Sep. 2020 to May. 2022 at University Of Virginia, Charlottesville, USA (GPA: 4.0)"
    />
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Experience</div>
  </div>

  <div class="time-line-container mb-10">
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Research Assistant at University of Virginia Riggs' Lab"
      subtitle="From Jan. 2021 to Present"
    >
    <ul>
      <li>
        - Built multiple <strong>VR/AR applications</strong> using <strong>Unity (C#)</strong> 
        and <strong>Android Studio</strong> for <strong>Meta Quest</strong>, 
        <strong>Microsoft HoloLens</strong>, and <strong>Magic Leap</strong>, 
        supporting <strong>multimodal input/output testing</strong> and 
        interactive task-switching environments.
      </li>
      <br>
      <li>
        - Led a series of mixed reality experiments analyzing cognitive workload 
        and multi-interface attention through <strong>multimodal data analysis</strong> 
        of eye tracking, movement tracking, and event logs using <strong>Python</strong> 
        and <strong>R</strong> for <strong>statistical modeling and visualization</strong>.
      </li>
      <br>
      <li>
        - Designed human-in-the-loop studies on AI-assisted decision-making, 
        using <strong>Python</strong> to clean data, extract behavioral metrics, 
        and <strong>model relationships between human performance, AI performance, 
        and collaboration modes</strong>.
      </li>
      <br>
      <li>
        - Developed a VR application to record and <strong>process 3D movement data</strong>, 
        integrating real-time sensor input and spatial tracking for 
        <strong>quantitative kinematic analysis</strong>.
      </li>
      <br>
    </ul>

    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Research Assistant at University of Virginia Ultimate User Interface Lab"
      subtitle="From Sep. 2021 to Sep. 2023"
    >
    <ul>
      <li>
        - Developed a <strong>computer vision–based sensing system</strong> to detect micro-movements and physical changes (e.g., force, volume) using <strong>Python</strong>, <strong>PyTorch</strong>, <strong>OpenCV</strong>, and convolutional neural networks informed by the Moiré pattern optical effect.
      </li>
      <br>
      <li>
        - Built <strong>processing pipelines</strong> for motion tracking and trained image recognition models to detect <strong>real-time physical interactions</strong>, enabling tangible interfaces via spatial gesture input, and integrated the system into self-developed <strong>Android</strong> and <strong>VR applications</strong>.
      </li>
      <br>
      <li>
        - Contributed to experimental design and VR prototyping to explore how VR-based perception manipulation influences proprioceptive accuracy during reaching tasks.
      </li>
      <br>
    </ul>

    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Research Assistant at University of Virginia Physics Department"
      subtitle="From May. 2022 to Sep. 2022"
    >
    <ul>
      <li>Created an interactive VR system in Unity for immersive science education, engineering 3D models and integrating physics-based animation pipelines to visualize real-time parton dynamics.</li>
    </ul>
    </TimeLineElement>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Publications</div>
  </div>

  <ul class="list-disc mx-6 mb-10 grid gap-3">
  <!-- Paper 1 -->
  <li>
    <a href="https://dl.acm.org/doi/abs/10.1145/3698113" target="_blank" class="font-semibold hover:underline">
      MoiréTag: A Low-Cost Tag for High-Precision Tangible Interactions without Active Components
    </a>
    <div class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
      <span class="font-medium">Authors:</span> Peiyu Zhang, Wen Ying, Sara L. Riggs, and Seongkook Heo
      <span class="block italic">ACM ISS 2024</span>
    </div>
  </li>
  </ul>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Skills</div>
  </div>

  <div class="mx-6">
    <!-- Languages & Frameworks -->
    <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 text-lg mb-2">Languages & Frameworks</h3>
    <ul class="list-disc md:columns-5 columns-2 mb-4">
      <li>Python</li>
      <li>Java</li>
      <li>C#</li>
      <li>SQL</li>
      <li>Kotlin</li>
      <li>JavaScript</li>
      <li>PyTorch</li>
      <li>React</li>
      <li>Node.js</li>
    </ul>

    <!-- Tools & Platforms -->
    <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 text-lg mb-2">Tools & Platforms</h3>
    <ul class="list-disc md:columns-5 columns-2">
      <li>Unity</li>
      <li>Android Studio</li>
      <li>AWS</li>
      <li>MongoDB</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

